body:
@grosser I have talked to @jeremy and he suggested to deprecate passing a class to `observe`. This will force everyone to use strings so we don't need to worry about supporting many different behaviors (if someone pass a class, just convert it to string and show the deprecation warning).

@grosser could you please also add a method like `AR::Observer.load_all!` (or in Active Model) that will load all observers? I am working on a configuration named `config.eager_load` and that should trigger `AR::Observer.load_all!`. Since this configuration will be true for test and production, we will be able to detect the "ClassThatDoesNotExist" case.

Finally, I agree with @dmathieu, if we could make symbols and strings to behave similarly, better.
